comment_regular_data.body: Well done! Thank you very much. There are a few minor failures on CI, but they are just reordering/reformatting things, so should be simple.

I'll work on this more later today. 

I think I'd probably change "standing together in a conference" back to "group", and then do a more general revision of the user manual in another pull request. I noticed the writing could use work, and this way we stay in the scope of this PR.
Sounds good, let's merge it and make a separate pr for more revision.

Looking at the CI failures, i'm not sure what I can do. Some simply timed out, and the `restyled` one had an error due to the length of the diff. 
For "build test and deploy", test_notificationgenerator failed and i'm not sure why. It seems like it is probably related to my changes. 
I'll come back to this tomorrow.
To fix the restyled issue, run clang-format (version 18) on the code: `clang-format-18 -i $(find src -name "*.h" -or -name "*.cpp")`

commit.message:
refactor: Rename Group Chat to Conference

Conference is the correct name per Tox protocol. Now that Tox has implemented new group chats, it is important to refer to conferences properly.
